comment: I was once a liason between a non profit organization I worked for and family courts in California. I'm going to call liar liar pants on fire for the nameless one, who "claims" 1. She was in constant danger from JD and that the LAPD was telling lies about the May 21st call and response...2. that she needed a TRO and then...3. "SHE" dropped the TRO. In California there are typically 3 Restraining Orders available.  1. EPO...Emergency Protective Order which the POLICE apply for immediately if they believe a victim is in immediate danger of abuse. It is signed and issued by a Judge as soon as the POLICE request it and it lasts 5-7 days until a hearing for a TRO....She never had a EPO, we know without a doubt that is because violence had not taken place as witnessed by Body Cam footage....2. the TRO is granted when a Judge believes you are in immediate danger and need protection until the court hears you case...the TRO is only in effect 20-25 days, when you go before the Judges a present your evidence for a Permanent restraining Order. She simply appeared in her make up and angry zit...said He beat me and had a friend say he beat her. TRO in place....3. Her TRO was withdrawn by the Judge with prejudice....that says a whole lot if you are paying attention. Thing is, Judges usually dismiss and withdraw without prejudice so the victim can reapply for the order if necessary later on...I kept wondering why JD's Legal team for his divorce had the body cam footage...I believe now it may have been presented to the Judge in the Restraining Order Case to prove that she lied to get the TRO and then the TRO quashed and the case dismissed with prejudice. IDK....just something that has been tumbling around in my brain...let me know what you think.
